NEWCASTLE DISEASE - BELARUS: OIE
********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 2 Jun 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Office International des Epizooties(OIE), Disease Information [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_17.HTM#Sec4>

Newcastle Disease in Belarus
-------------------------------
(Date of previous outbreak of Newcastle disease in Belarus reported
to the OIE: 1980).
Emergency report
Translation of information received on 30 May 2003 from Dr Aleksandr
Makarovitch Aksionov, Head of Veterinary Services, Ministry of
Agriculture and Food, Minsk:
Report date: 28 May 2003.
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 16 May 2003.
Estimated date of first infection: 15 May 2003.
Outbreaks:
Location: Doubline, Gomel Region, Braguinsk district
Description of affected population: private farms.
Total number of animals in the outbreaks:
species/ susceptible/ cases/ deaths/ destroyed/ slaughtered
avi/ 12 464 / 1 / 213 /.../...
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: National Veterinary
Laboratory for avian diseases.
B. Diagnostic tests used: virological tests on embryonating chicken eggs.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: unknown.
B. Mode of spread: unknown.
Control measures:
- Quarantine;
- vaccination;
- movement control inside the country.
--
